        "authorId" : "919d650d-5f9e-4069-90f7-968e2cf7bb16",
        "body" : "Is there a way to get the linter to ignore docstring output examples?\r\n\r\nThe numpydoc [style guide](https://numpydoc.readthedocs.io/en/latest/format.html), which we adhere to, still mentions 80 characters. How does scipy deal with exceptions, especially as now the CI will not run the rest of the jobs?",
